text:
I have the “29 Lyk-blue” color option in this hoodie. That design is a colorful nebula on a black background. The space design starts at the shoulders, goes onto the sleeves, and flows down the body of the hoodie. The back of the hoodie has the same nebula. The hood is plain black; one of the product photos shows the hood as having the design and a different photo shows it as plain black. The hood is lined with black.

The sizing is about an inch smaller than the size chart. I have a size small hoodie. After washing, the chest measurement is approximately 41 inches. The size chart says size small is 42.6 inches. The hoodie narrows at the waist, that measurement is 34 inches.

I usually wear a men’s small in tees and sweatshirts; I expected this hoodie would run small. It fits, but I can feel it pulling at the back if I cross my arms. The hoodie has a little stretch but not a lot. It’s made from a mix of 95% polyester and 5% spandex.

It’s a lightweight hoodie, so it’s not super warm. The material is kind of slick, or maybe slippery is a better way to describe it. It’s not fleecy or sweatshirt material.

The care tag says to hand wash, I don’t know anyone that’s going to hand wash a hoodie. The description says machine wash, and that’s what I did. The hoodie did not shrink in the washer or dryer, and the print didn’t fade at all.

There are a few construction issues on my hoodie. The seams are puckered around the kangaroo pocket, so there’s a permanent wrinkle. The seam on the top of the hood is stretched out, so I can see some of the stitches.

Have a difficult time rating this dress. Was looking for something simple and long, not too clingy (to hide my many flaws!) to wear to a casual outdoor wedding, and really liked the look, particularly the modest scoop neckline. Ordered a large (I'm 5'-7", 155 lbs, typically wear a size 14 and a 36C bra.) According to the size chart, a large correlated to my usual dress size ("12-14"), might possibly be a bit big in the top ("38.5-40"), but I've usually found that anything with Spandex (5%) usually fits a little more snugly.

When it arrived, initial impression was good - nice and soft feel - until I tried it on. The top was VERY snug, the waist was more right below my bustline versus at the waist (as shown in the photo with the model), and though I loved the flow of the skirt, I would have to be over six feet tall to wear this dress unaltered - even with the highest heels possible! Since the wedding is outdoors with chairs on the lawn, women had been advised to wear flats, and in that case, this dress was going to have to be hemmed a full SIX INCHES (and would still hit the floor!) I remembered being confused by the reviews... a woman my height (5'-7") said it was @ 1/2" off the ground... a 5'-8" said it reached her ankles... a 5'-9" said it reached the tops of her feet but didn't drag the ground... a 5'-10" said it was too long even with heels --- how could these women all be experiencing such different things? Once on Amazon I'd mistakenly ordered a dress for my granddaughter by an imposter, and I wondered if possibly the same thing had happened here. But there's only one seller, "OLRIK", and orders are fulfilled by Amazon.

Well, I just now looked at the "Certificate of Achievement" on this listing, 5 photos down, and there was the clue as to why there are such discrepancies with what women were experiencing. Here's what it says (complete with misspellings and actual punctuations): "All authentic levaca products sold through AMAZON.com are sold only by the seller OLRIK. Prouducts that sole by other sellers are imitation products similar in design. Please take note. these unauthentic products does not have same quality such as color.tabic. construction and over all design and feel as our products. levaca does not support the quality assurance of these products. Hence. Please check the name of seller before purchasing these products. levaca takes authenticty of product very seriously and will take legal action against all lmitation products and will further take possible action with Amazon.com." It seems the lack of attention to detail in the "Certificate of Achievement" is reflected in the product itself, which is obviously hit or miss.

For 20 bucks, you can always take a chance (like I did) that you get one that fits; if you don't, you can return it (like I am.)

text: These shoes are great!  Every 10th person my 1.5yo son walks past says they want a pair.  And they’re usually adults.  Got the gold, thinking they’d be cool shoes even if the lights didn’t work.  But they work gloriously!  The usb splitter charges them well, the remote gives a lot of…control.  Remotely.  It does allow access to a lot of features that would be harder to pull up (or unavailable) just using the shoes’ buttons.  There are 15 unique colors that can be selected on the remote, and four modes that will cycle through all the colors.  Fade is my favorite, has very smooth transitions.  Am already planning to use these as accent lights around the house once my son outgrows them.  My only concern at this point is that he will jump in a puddle and fry the circuit.  Would be cool if they came out with waterproof ones that had silicone inserts for the ports when not charging, like some phone cases.  No complaints though, worth every penny.

text:
I’d say the Amazon Essentials Active Sculpt High Rise Leggings run at least a size small. My mom normally wears an X-Large, but when she tried these on, in size X-Large, she could barely get them up. The leggings were incredibly unflattering on her, and she had them on all of five minutes before taking them off because she didn’t like the fit. Out of curiosity, I tried them on and the X-Large almost fit me -- and I wear a size medium.

There’s nothing “sculpting” about these leggings. They are soft and stretchy, which is great -- they are comfortable if the size is right. But they don’t tuck you in anywhere.

I like the flap top cargo pockets. They actually fit a big phone, I tried with my Note 20 Ultra to see if it would fit, and it does. So iPhones and other smaller phones definitely fit. The flap top pockets could also be used for money or wallets, whatever’s inside shouldn’t fall out and there aren’t any zippers to poke against your legs.

The leggings are easy care: machine wash cold, tumble dry low or line dry. There is a bundle of six care tags on the back waist seam.

details: {'Package Dimensions': '6 x 4.9 x 1.3 inches; 6.4 Ounces', 'Item model number': 'UK_B002HZZLU0', 'Department': 'Womens', 'Date First Available': 'April 24, 2020', 'Manufacturer': 'Carolyn Pollack'}
text: Although every thing that the other reviewers have said about this necklace is quite true, to me these facts do not add up to a negative.  I really like this necklace.  The chunkiness goes well with chunky Carolyn Pollack enhancers, and it does not droop around your neck, but it lays in a circle.  After a day of supporting an enhancer, it does bend down a little bit.  Personally, I have no trouble with the lobster claw clasp.  I guess you either do well with them or you don't.  The cord is a nice braided bronze color, but has no silver in it.  The silver is in the fittings.  Why they made a bronze end for the necklace, and didn't just stick to bronze for the chain is beyond me, because it is true that where two metals touch, corrosion occurs.  The fact that the ends of the necklace are chunky doesn't pose a problem for Carolyn Pollack jewelry, because most of the enhancers have a clasp that opens.  Overall, I like this piece, and would recommend it.

title_y: Ridiculously Small And See Through (Size Up At LEAST Two Sizes)
text:
I originally got this because I needed some more summer tops. When I got it, I could not believe it. I thought it would at least fit. I was wrong.

SIZE
I got a size XL which is supposed to be a 16-18. It looked like it would be big enough. It was not at all. It was so tight in the bust that I could barely get it on. I wear a size 16 misses US. This is not anywhere near a size 16.

MEASUREMENTS OF BUST ON ACTUAL TOP
The top measures 36 inches when the top is stretch to capacity.

FABRIC
The fabric is very see through almost transparent cotton. It is woven not knit.

STYLE
The style is cute, but it runs so small, I would say get 2 sizes up if you want it to be roomy and give enough room to wear a cami under it.

WASHING
Washing leads it to shrink even more. When washed in cold water and air dried it got smaller.

CONSTRUCTION
The construction was also not great. Facings were not sewn down and flipped all around instead of laying flat.

WHO WEARS IT?
This top barely fits the size 12 girl I asked to try it on.

THE BOTTOM LINE
This is cute in style, but the fabric is see through, the top runs way too small, and this was a frustrating experience.

MY RATING
ONE STAR. This had potential but disappointed greatly in many ways.

title_y: OMG- I LOVE THESE PANTS- So Does My Husband
text:
My husband has a rocker look. That makes it hard to find clothing sometimes because he is not into the slobby look so many musicians are into. He likes unusual colors and designs and can pull them off both in clothing and jewelry.

FABRIC
The fabric that these are made of is cotton for sure. It is a light to medium weight cotton so you won't roast if you wear them in warmer weather.

STYLE
These run pretty true to size, but if you are between sizes, go up one. They might shrink. The pockets were plenty deep enough so that was not a problem either.

GIVE
These have plenty of give in them so that they are comfortable to wear. You will need a belt with them, so be ready for that.

COLORS
I did not expect there to be purple in these, but it is there. It is pretty nice touch to the blue, black, and white. There is also a darker blue too.

PERFORMANCE
These were comfortable and my husband loved wearing them on our day out. People were going crazy over his outfit and loved it. He got endless compliments.

THE BOTTOM LINE
These are great if you can wear skinny jeans, are more of a slimmer fit person and can pull off artistic or rocker looks. Put with the right shirt, these pants are epic.

MY RATING
FIVE STARS. These pants are just what I have been looking for for my husband. He was not sure at first until the entire outfit came together. He kept getting so many compliments that he now feels much happier about wearing this crazy pair of pants with the right shirt.

title_y: Bring New Life to Your Purse or Handbag
text:
Purse straps often fall into disrepair. You could ditch everything and get a new purse or handbag, but if the purse or bag itself is still fine, why not salvage it instead? This VanEnjoy Pair Genuine Leather Purses Strap Handles Replacement is designed to do exactly that.

You get a pair of straps with this set. The straps are made with cowhide leather, and they utilize a lobster clasp. There are two so, depending on your needs, you could use both on a single purse or use one each on two different purses or bags. Two is best for purses, and it makes gripping and holding better, but you could go with one depending on the type of bag.

The lobster clasps on these straps take some effort to squeeze, but once in place, they seem to grip well and are unlikely to come loose, since it does take effort. The clasps are a brass- like color, which means they should match well with just about any purse.

If your purse straps or handbag straps are worn out, this set by VanEnjoy could be just what you need. So far everything seems okay, but only time will tell if they hold up, they way I hope they will. They are good from what I can tell, especially for this price point.

text: I think it's a great concept and as a whole I like them. I like the fact that there's no tail and they are adjustable. Exactly what I was looking for but I found two downsides for me. First, even at it's tightest setting, they are still too big for me. It does prevent my glasses from falling off my face, but because it's still loose they still go halfway down the bridge of my nose. When I would rest my head on the back of my couch, they would push forward so I wasn't able to rest my head while watching tv. Also once you put these on your glasses, trying to get them off was quite a challenge. Kudos to the company for making them so secure, but I thought I was going to break the arms of my glasses trying to get them off, but I eventually did. So...overall I would recommend this product, maybe I just have a small head. LOL.

title_y: Extremely comfortable and made in the USA
text:
These compression socks are manufactured right here in the good old USA! Kudos to this company for not outsourcing!

These knee-high socks are 15-20 mmHg, mild-compression socks, which is no doubt why they are labeled as primarily travel socks. People who have specific health issues usually choose socks with a higher level of compression than these. I myself wear compression socks because I stand or walk up to 12 hours a day, and compression socks at this level of compression successfully prevent tired and sore feet, shin splints and cramps in my calves.

The fabric in these socks, which is Polyester/Spandex, is very soft and, as advertised, it is stretchy enough to make it much easier to put these socks on than many other brands of compression socks. But even so, these socks are not so stretchy that it compromises firm support.

I love the feel of this fabric. It is so smooth and comfy, it is a pleasure both to put on these socks and to wear them. I don't think I've ever felt fabric of this high quality in any compression socks I've ever worn, and I've tried out at least eight different brands at this point.

Note that these are casual socks rather than dress socks. The compression socks I own which are sold as dress socks are made of a lighter-weight fabric than these. These socks might be a bit too heavyweight to be worn at the height of summer in a situation without air conditioning.

The top of these socks is designed in such a way that it stays firmly in place, without drooping, while avoiding being so tight it impedes blood circulation.

The heel and toe of these socks are reinforced, but they do not poke or bind my toes.

The sizing on these socks is accurate. I ordered the size I normally wear, and it fits perfectly.

These socks are available in multiple fashion designs and colors to suit many different tastes. They can be purchased as a single pair, which is the case with these particular socks, or in a 3-pack with a variety of designs among the several pairs of socks.

While it is possible to wash these socks in a washing machine and put them in the dryer, I would never do that myself, because that amount of rigorous handling will cause them to wear out much, much sooner. Instead, I hand wash all of my compression socks in warm water with mild soap, rinse them well, gently squeeze out excess water, and hang them up to dry. Given that these socks are black, I place an old towel beneath them to catch the several, inevitable drips of black dye so that they don't stain my tub.

title_y: Fun moves, but combinations tricky to follow
text:
I love kickboxing--in fact, it's one of the few forms of cardio that I truly enjoy. Unfortunately, I found this DVD to be disappointing. The moves themselves were fun and the combinations were mostly interesting, but I did not click at all with the teaching style of the instructor, Ilaria Montagnani. In this workout, Ilaria teaches very LONG combinations of punches and kicks. Although she teaches in an "add-on" style, starting with a few moves and then adding on new moves, each time she goes back to the beginning, she does NOT cue the moves! For example, she will simply say "let's start again," and then the reviewer is expected to recall all the moves up to that point WITHOUT Ilaria saying what they are. This is made even more difficult by the camera angles--e.g., sometimes the camera is focusing on Ilaria from the waist up only, so you can't see the kicks that she is doing.

If each combination was short and repeated many times, this might not be such an issue, but as noted above, the combos are quite lengthy. I have described each below. To make matters worse, the combinations are DIFFERENT on each side of the body--in her Introduction, Ilaria says that this does not matter, as you will be doing about the same number of punches and kicks, but it definitely felt uneven to me. All times listed are approximately.

WARM-UP (5 minutes)
Mostly alternating punches front, including jab, cross punch, hook, and upper cut. The front push kick is included as well, but no other kicks are practiced in the warm-up. I set of push-ups is performed at the end.

PUNCHES (7 minutes)
Here Ilaria introduces a long punch combination. The combination is performed for many sets (12-16?) on one side, then repeated on the second side. These are the punches (slashes denote where each piece is added on):
jab-jab-cross / hook-cross / upper-cross / fast 3 right-fast 3 left / jab-cross

KICKS (10.5 minutes)
This was more drills than combinations and was easier to follow. Ilaria begins with a front chamber/front kick. Next is a side chamber/roundhouse, building up to three roundhouse kicks. The third kick was the crescent, starting with alternating knees to the side and then adding in the crescent. Finally, the side kick was performed with a chamber/side kick, then moving on to a double knee/side kick/squat.

COMBINATION #1, LEFT SIDE (6.5 minutes)
knee-double front push kick / opposite knee crescent / walk around, opposite knee roundhouse / squat-roundhouse-knee / double roundhouse / jab-cross hook-cross upper-cross

COMBINATION #2, RIGHT SIDE (6 minutes)
jab-jab-cross / front push kick, 2x / opposite leg crescent / walk around, opposite leg roundhouse / squat, roundhouse x3

COMBINATION #3, face forward (10 minutes)
hi level block to side / mid level block to side / alternating sides with side kicks / karate punches

STRETCH (3 minutes)
This is a very brief segment that includes a low back release, a lunge for the hip flexors, a standing side stretch/backbend, and a standing triceps stretch. It did not feel adequate given the overall length of the workout (over 50 minutes).

I actually liked the moves in Combo #3 the most, but I also found this combination to be the MOST frustrating! Ilaria's cuing seemed almost totally random here, as I could never figure out which side she was going to next; I don't think she worked the sides evenly at all. It didn't help that the music sometimes would drown her out (and on top of that, I found her accent sometimes difficult to understand as well). I will say that Ilaria DID give excellent form pointers throughout the workout. Personally, however, I wish she would have spent more time actually cuing the moves themselves.

title_y: Compression in all the right places; helps with my plantar fasciitis; runs large
text:
I have plantar fasciitis and have been trying and using various compression socks and sleeves and arch inserts to help reduce the pain and prevent a recurrence once the pain is gone.

These socks are not only stylish, but they feel great on and actually have compression in the arch area. There is also good compression in the calf area. 

I ordered the large/extra-large because I take a 9 to 9.5 shoe. However, I find that these are a bit long (and looser than their small/medium) as I have to roll the top over to prevent it from coming above my knee. They fit me perfectly, otherwise. However, since they are on the large side, I'm passing them off to my boyfriend. I have several pairs of these socks and have worn their socks all day. It feels great wearing them. I also love the styles they come in.

These are not only "fun" but they are medically helpful for my plantar fasciitis. I wash socks like these in a lingerie bag and lay them flat to dry. Currently, there is no price listed on Amazon for these socks but I would expect them to be priced in the $12.99 to $16.99 range. The only reason I lowered my rating one star is because they are larger than the size specified; otherwise, these are 5-star socks in my opinion.

But if you're just in the market for a coat, choose another one. You'll just end up with a pile of cheap fabric and an hole in your savings!

A recent embrace of style had spurred the realization that my sock collection was rather blasé, consisting mostly of hard-worn gold-toe fluffies and other generic socks. Esteemed sock manufacturer, James Fiallo, rectified my issues by providing this convenient 12 pack assortment of startlingly interesting socks. The patterns are colorful, as indeed claimed, but also tasteful and I've received more complements than snickers (not that it would stop me, anyway) upon donning myself of the aforementioned footwear. There are plenty of colors to match with different colored pants and shoes, several blacks and blues along with many mid-hue green/orange/yellow and several purple colors as well. Socks are an average thickness, but closer to dress socks than athletic socks, not for working out, only for style. They provide just about no warmth, so prepare some warm shoes if you are prone to cold feet (in the empirical, as opposed to metaphorical, sense). My only other complaint is that two of the pairs are exceptionally small, considerably more so than the others, reducing their 'ability-to-be-put-on' status to 'impossible' (for my feet, a solid US 12, at least).

I'm happy, and will likely purchase again from sock manufacturer extraordinaire, James Fiallo.

title_y: Perfect comfort bra for this 36DD bust
text: I was hesitant to purchase a One Size Fits All set of bras especially considering the varying reviews, but they fit me just as I wanted. I am 5'6, medium build, size 10 in clothing, and range between a 34DD and 36DD depending on the brand/style of bra. I did not purchase these as sports bras because they definitely would not have enough support to be considered sports bras for larger bust sizes, but I purchased these as comfort bras. I wear them around the house, under tank tops for added support and a pop of color, and out and about for errands. I did not have any issues with bulging under the arms or being too tight in the bust. The pads cover the exact area I would want them to.  The pads do bend if put in the washer, but I now use the handwash cycle and then hang dry and haven't had an issue since!  The colors have stayed true through washing and even the bright red did not bleed.  I would recommend them to other women solely as comfort bras when you're tired of underwire, but need some daily support.  I also have comfort pull-over bras by Hanes and Barely There and I would say these definitely compare in comfort, but go one step further and offer more color options.

details: {'Is Discontinued By Manufacturer': 'No', 'Package Dimensions': '4.7 x 4.2 x 3.1 inches; 12.8 Ounces', 'Item model number': 'DOM698SM', 'Department': 'Mens', 'Date First Available': 'June 4, 2015', 'Manufacturer': 'findtime'}
text:
This is a lovely piece, but I wish it were larger. I noticed that this seller offers very similar watches in a slightly larger size (this watch is 35 mm and the others are 38.5 mm). On most men, these others will look better. [[ASIN:B00ORJGIOC Findtime Mens Silver Luminous Tungsten Steel Quartz Wrist Watches]].

[[ASIN:B00ORJGEV4 Findtime Mens Silver Tungsten Steel Luxury Luminous Quartz Wrist Watches]]. Nonetheless, the description accurately described the dimensions, and for what it is, it has earned 5 stars.

First off, if you've looked at any of the other reviews, the big question on your mind is, "how fragile is this thing?" The seller makes a big deal in the description about not dropping the watch because it WILL shatter, not ifs, ands, or buts about it. As such, I haven't been willing to drop mine to find out. However, I TOOK A VERY SHARP KNIFE to the under side (just in case) of the watch band and tried hard to scratch it and couldn't. I'm satisfied that the band will keep looking brand new, so long as I (or my kids) don't drop it.

PROS:
- looks very handsome. The size is small enough for a woman, but when my wife tried it on, we both agreed it just looks masculine. That's impressive given how tiny it is by today's standards.
- sits very low to the wrist. This means it fits under ANY dress shirt cuff you've got.
- shockingly comfortable
- versatile (but mostly dressy)
- butterfly clasp is a cool feature
- easy to size (if you have the tools. I use one like this [[ASIN:B002Q8AJSM SE JT6218 5-Piece Watch Band Link Pin Tool Set]])
- Date window (warning: it is basically invisible to anyone with struggling eyesight)
- strong, multifaceted sapphire crystal (glass covering the face). This is perhaps my favorite part of the watch. I love how the different geometric cuts catch light. See my photos if that didn't make sense.

CONS:
- shows all fingerprints badly (face, bracelet, everywhere)
- tiny crown looks nice, but is awkward to turn when setting the time/date
- very small by modern men's watch trend standards.

WHAT I'D CHANGE:
- It's too small. I think this watch with a 40 mm face would be stunning!
- slightly bigger, more tactile crown

BOTTOM LINE: lovely watch, especially if you have a small wrist, but the bigger options above may be better for everyone else and whatever you do DON'T DROP IT!!!

I received a complimentary unit for testing. My review is my own and is in no way influenced by anyone connected to the design or sale of this item.

When it stays on with two bobby pins, I wake up to lovely, not tangled, not frizzy hair. The addition of an adjustable strap would have made this 5 STARS. title_y: A way to show connection- physically + metaphorically!! just perfect!
text:
Super sweet and Super clever! This is a fun twist on “a matching bracelet set.” Plus, something PIPITREE has addressed quite well.. And that is create a style of jewelry that is made for BOTH genders alike!

Many of these “matching combos” miss the mark! So, be sure to take into account the aesthetics of the jewelry and who is receiving it while choosing! It needs to be pleasing to male/female. If not- it’s a bust and a classic example of why “matching couples jewelry” can morph into “couples keychains” instead!!

Sizing fits! These can adjust by the slip of their knots. Ohh, and can be put on using one hand. These could go in h2o BUT.. I wouldn’t recommend!! silver charms will tarnish/discolor- water speeds up that process.. So, slip off before you shower, swim, etc!

Engraving is tiny, delicate and legible!! Mine includes two languages and a shape. I love that- Silver bead can twist showing its various sides.. and 2 beads placed together, they make a “whole/complete” charm. Aahh..!!

**The most clever touch is the tiny magnet charm. Seriously, if holding hands these magnets connect and it’s the cutest thing ever..!! Whatever bracelet says or looks like, this is the winning factor. IF you think why you’re giving matching bracelets.. its to show your connection- right?!!

Physically/metaphorically this bracelet set works for BFF, SISTERS, TRUE LOVE, ETC. seeing them in action, Im certain they’ll be well received!! At $10 price point- Basically, you get 2 string bracelets, 2 metal beads, with magnets.. BUT, its the symbolism and
meaning behind it that you’re really paying for! I hope this info can help your decision.. Feel free to let me know!

title_x: Boa nerve, stealth
videos: [{'title': "Whatever you're packing the Stealth will carry it for you ... in style", 'url': 'https://www.amazon.com/vdp/9df2d87d195c4cdf8b760f9863fb2489?ref=dp_vse_rvc_0', 'user_id': 'AHQFUXIYQ4YTRQN6WLWV4XU5P3JA'}]
details: {'Is Discontinued By Manufacturer': 'No', 'Product Dimensions': '19.7 x 5.1 x 14.2 inches; 3.3 Pounds', 'Item model number': 'BNL-STH', 'Date First Available': 'October 27, 2014'}
text:
I own a number of Booq products, so when I was offered a review sample of this new model I accepted. Like all Booq bags the emphasis is on efficient management of space as well as protecting electronics. This bag is no exception.

First, unlike the other bags that I own this one is kind of complicated, In fact, the shoulder strap and stabilizer strap design drove me crazy at first. Even the instruction card was of little help. Basically I had problems grasping how the magnetic buckle and stabilizing straps were designed for, as well as the fact that the shoulder pad on the strap hid the magnetic buckle when I first unboxed it. I finally figured it out with patience and carefully studying the diagrams.

Second, at first I thought the shoulder and stabilizer straps were poorly designed. I was wrong. They are designed for perfect ergonomics and balance. Again, this is a learning curve issue. In some ways Booq has been too clever in the design because there is a complexity that takes time to learn. For me it's worth it because I can carry a relatively heavy load (about thirty pounds) in a balanced fashion and still be assured that the tablet and a few other electronic odds and ends I carry are well protected. Protection is one area where Booq excels.

This is not trendy fine leather. Vegans will love it, and while I do not know exactly what it is, it's some sort of durable plastic material that is superbly constructed. The stitching, webbing, clasps and zippers are all first rate. Water literally rolls off it, and the reflective piping is a nice touch with respect to safety, whether walking or cycling.

Organizational options and features are another Booq hallmark. Instead of my trying to describe them in detail, look at the product photos on this page. There is a place for everything, and it has been well thought out. I've had this bag for a week and am still discovering compartments.

Bottom line: this is a bag that does take time to learn. It probably should come with a video or a link to one, which will make it immediately useful because I can assure you that the first day of ownership will be frustrating. Take your time and learn it because after that you will love it totally.
